		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I believe the MMC5 pinout shows an address line to PRG for a ROM as big as 1 Megabyte. I'm not sure if the ROM socket on any PCB has it connected though. Why do you need 1 Megabyte of PRG? You can accomplish this with MMC1 being wired similar to SXROM/SUROM. Or by wiring up a UxROM type board to have more PRG register bits.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


